                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-off1563" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-off1563" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18261207-270-cd1564" type="crimeDate">18th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-270-off1563 t18261207-270-cd1564"></join>, 1 wooden-box, value 1s. 6d.; 1 book, value 1s.; 34 pots of tomato-paste, value 3l., and 4 ozs. of gum-paste ornaments, value 2s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18261207-270-victim1471" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  Russell
               <interp inst="t18261207-270-victim1471" type="surname" value="Russell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-victim1471" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-victim1471" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-270-off1563 t18261207-270-victim1471"></join>
                  </persName>
            , and others.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261207-270-person1472">
                  JOHN 
                  CHASE
               <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1472" type="surname" value="CHASE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1472" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1472" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am book-keeper to T. Russell and others, who are <rs id="t18261207-270-viclabel1565" type="occupation">carriers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-270-victim1471 t18261207-270-viclabel1565"></join>, and live in Friday-street, Cheapside. On the 18th of November the prisoner came into the office, and asked if the Colchester waggon went from there - I said, No; and as he went out I saw him take a box - I went into the yard, and asked the porters if he had brought one in - they said, No; I called to him; he took no notice - I sent the porters after him; they brought him back, and he said he had taken the wrong box, and it was heavier than the one he brought - I told him to put it down where he took it from, and take the one he had brought; he could not find that; he was a stranger; the one he took had come from Plymouth, and contained this property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261207-270-person1473">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1473" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1473" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261207-270-person1473" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter at this inn. I saw the prisoner come up the yard; he had no box; he came out of the warehouse with one; Chase sent me after him, and he said he had made a mistake; he returned with me, and put it down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261207-270-person1474">
